originalText.text: An amazing chair massage by Katie. It was hard to communicate but she got the message that I was hoping for a hard massage and boy she went deep-tissue! It was 30 minutes but felt longer and she was focused the whole time. My shoulders and back felt much better after. With their generous 15% holiday discount it only ended up being $33, a total steal, so I tipped generously. If I lived here I'd go every other week. Gotta get lucky to find a massage spot that clicks, believe me I've been trying to find one forever in SF.

originalText.text: This is a massage place not a spa and it’s important to understand the difference for what you are looking for. The key to this place is the prices are low. The massage was certainly not the best and it certainly was not the worst. The hot stones were great, the elbows into my spine were not. No where else in NYC can you get an hour for under 60 dollars (tax included).

originalText.text: We really like this spot. The staff are so nice and quality of massage is so good. The place is very clean and staff wear mask. We liked the massage table it’s comfortable. They take card and classpass. In nice location. Prices are regular of massages medium price level. Will go back regular.

originalText.text:
Did a walk in last night and it was amazing.  I was feeling very sore, especially in my calves and feet, from walking around the city all day: and the massage made me feel good as new.  The staff was very polite, and took me into a room immediately. The massage therapist was professional, and adjusted the pressure when I asked.

There is a bit of ambient noise since the rooms are not fully covered,  but it wasn’t too bothersome. There was no pressure to tip but I happily did so because the service was excellent.

originalText.text:
Absolutely two of the best Chinese massages I have enjoyed outside of China. First a foot massage, which was so good that I returned for a back + head massage.

They do NOT offer "special services",  & have a sign on the check-in wall: "SERIOUS MASSAGE, NO HANKY PANKY". now you know why to go, and why to stay away.

Another reason to go = very fair prices. At the time of posting, $58 for 1 hour, & 1 hour can be two 30-minute massages combined.

I am adding to this review to respond to some of the harsh criticism. First  there was no mention of a required tip, or tip rate. If they were doing this earlier  I suspect it was because they were advised this was the way to run the business. They clearly know better now
Second, I have traveled throughout China, collectively spending more than 3 years there  and enjoyed many massages at the Chinese saunas. Their standard assumption is that people prefer that the masseuse be of the opposite sex. If you do not want that  just inform them when you arrive, or when your masseuse arrives and you realize that you forgot to specify!
